Class ConflictController

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.wpruszak.blitzch.controller.ConflictController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConflictGetter, ConflictResolver

    public class ConflictController
extends Object
implements ConflictGetter, ConflictResolver
    Controller responsible for all the operations with finding and resolving git conflicts.

    This controller conflict finders:

    • InteractiveConflictSolutionFinderImpl

      • getAllConflicts

        public List<String> getAllConflicts(String[] lines)
                             throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: ConflictGetter
        Returns list of String representations of all the git conflicts in given String lines array.

        For example for file looking like this: File.php

                        <<<<<<<< HEAD
                something
                =======
                something more
                >>>>>>>> branch

        Would return list of String elements like this: 

                        something
                =======
                something more
        Specified by:
        getAllConflicts in interface ConflictGetter
        Parameters:
        lines - of the file
        Returns:
        List<String> of all the git conflicts within given lines
        Throws:
        IOException - if I/O is corrupted
        See Also:
        ConflictGetter

      • automaticResolveConflictsInFile

        public void automaticResolveConflictsInFile(FileBean fileBean,
                                            String mode)
                                     throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: ConflictResolver
        Automatically resolves all of the git conflicts in a given file accordingly to given mode.

        This method will not ask for any permission, it will solve the conflicts itself and overwrite the file with the final result. Depending on mode given to it as a parameter the results will differ (or may differ).

        Specified by:
        automaticResolveConflictsInFile in interface ConflictResolver
        Parameters:
        fileBean - file to solve conflicts for
        mode - of conflict solving
        Throws:
        IOException - if I/O is corrupted
        See Also:
        ConflictResolver

      • interactiveResolveConflictsInFile

        public void interactiveResolveConflictsInFile(FileBean fileBean)
                                       throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: ConflictResolver
        Interactive conflict resolving in file, whenever this method encounters git conflict it will ask what to do. Mode given to this method is interactive by default.

        After encountering conflict there will be these options:

        • Keep newer conflict version
        • Keep older conflict version
        • Keep both conflict versions, first new then old
        • Keep both conflict versions, first old then new
        • Manually fix the conflict
        Specified by:
        interactiveResolveConflictsInFile in interface ConflictResolver
        Parameters:
        fileBean - file to solve conflicts for
        Throws:
        IOException - if I/O is corrupted
        See Also:
        ConflictResolver
